            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Worst school of Gurgaon in terms of Management and i must say in academics which is degrading day-by-day and extra curricular activities also as many of the parents moved out from this school branch because of that. Pre-primary wing is somehow OK but for others (class-1 onwards), very poor facilities, whether it's hygeine in classrooms or washrooms.\nStaff is very rude and don't even have etiquettes to talk especially Pawan Sharma who is coordinator for admissions/renewals, always trying to trap the parents by offering different fee structure even for the same class. Playground is very small, not at all sufficient even for morning classes assembly, so forget about outdoor games which is a must for students and almost all the schools are providing. It's almost 5 yrs. now since this school branch is operational but nothing has improved here. In case any concern is being raised, no action at all from the management. Principal is always silent, doesn't matter whatever the issue is. Not sure whether Principal is really exists in this school or not. I don't know why they are spoiling the career/future of the students by such kind of practices. I think this school only cares about their fees, which is different for every individual.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
